@database "ChangeName.guide"
@author "Andy Macklin"
@remark "$VER: ChangeName Guide 1.0 (17. August 1997)"
@index INDEX

@node Main "Hi"

This is a quick script knocked up to resolve the recurrent problem of
people wanting to use a different email address for news & email, in order
to filter out unwanted mail sent to the email address used in the news
postings.

It is @{b}@{u}NOT@{uu}@{ub} intended as a means of replacing a valid
address with an invalid one. If you do not have your own domain name then
this script will probably be of no use. If you do have your own domain
name then please do not use it to change your newsgroup address to an invalid one.

@{"Requirements " link Req}
