@node Req "Requirements"

Thor 2.5 pre 1 or better  (as if you needed an excuse to register/upgrade)
    This allows you to use the From: header
These shell commands in your path somewhere:
    Echo
    Type
    Delete

@endnode

@node INDEX "Index"


@{"Main" link Main}
@{"Requirements " link Req}
@{"Usage" link Use}
@{"Legal" link Legal}
@{"Author" link Auth}

@endnode
@node Use "Usage"

Run this script just before you make your connection to your ISP. It will
only run @{u}once@{uu} per session, so make sure that you have written all
of the news postings that you want before you run it.

Syntax:
ChangeName.br <system> <new email address>

<system> is the Thor system that contains the news postings
<new email address> must be the full address
    e.g. TASC@toadhall.u-net.com

Limitations:
The first time that the script is run it sets an env: variable in env:thor.
The existance of this is checked before the script changes anything & if
the variable is set then nothing happens. I don't think that there's likely
to be much call for multisystem news posting, but if someone needs it then
it's easy to add.

There's no way to reverse the change, except by hand.

@endnode
